01:00:22,020 --> 01:00:25,020
what is the rest mass of the box of gas?

1344
01:00:25,020 --> 01:00:26,020
The answer is,

1345
01:00:26,020 --> 01:00:28,020
if you increase the energy

1346
01:00:28,020 --> 01:00:30,020
by adding thermal energy,

1347
01:00:30,020 --> 01:00:33,020
you add a certain number of calories,

1348
01:00:33,020 --> 01:00:35,020
or a certain number of joules,

1349
01:00:35,020 --> 01:00:37,020
joules is a unit of energy,

1350
01:00:37,020 --> 01:00:39,020
you add a certain amount of energy,

1351
01:00:39,020 --> 01:00:41,020
you add a certain amount of energy,

1352
01:00:41,020 --> 01:00:43,020
you add a certain amount of energy,

1353
01:00:43,020 --> 01:00:45,020
and you add a certain amount of energy.

1354
01:00:45,020 --> 01:00:48,020
And so you can measure the mass of the box.

1355
01:00:48,020 --> 01:00:51,020
You will discover that the box is mass.

1356
01:00:51,020 --> 01:00:53,020
The box of gas, its mass increases.

1357
01:00:53,020 --> 01:00:55,020
Its weight increases.

1358
01:00:55,020 --> 01:00:58,020
Now, the amount that it would increase

1359
01:00:58,020 --> 01:01:00,020
is so tiny,

1360
01:01:00,020 --> 01:01:02,020
if you increase the temperature

